==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indri
<hw>In"dri</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any lemurine animal of the
genus <gen>Indris</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Several species are known, all of them natives of
Madagascar, as the diadem indris (<spn>Indris diadema</spn>), which has
a white ruff around the forehead; the woolly indris (<spn>Indris
laniger</spn>); and the short-tailed or black indris (<spn>Indris
brevicaudatus</spn>), which is black, varied with gray.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indubious</ent>⟦br⟧
